Police on Thursday rescued a five-month-old infant from an alleged child-trafficking ring in Lucky Summer Estate. Two women, Rahab Wanjiru and Mercy Mburu were also arrested. One of the ladies is a director of a Children's Home in Mathare. She is alleged to have trafficked the child in the pretense of foster care. The DCI in a tweet confirmed the child is in safe custody. The suspects will be arraigned on Friday. Click here for the latest political news